Early_LaJolla_CO2_technical_report_1957-1962.pdf
This file contains measurements of CO2 concentration (ppm) on the X08A scale at La Jolla,
California from September 9, 1958 through October 10, 1962. The raw data occasionally had
more than 48 measurement points in a day and so these raw times were then linearly
interpolated onto a 48 measurement point day half-hour time scale centered on the
half hours.  Methods of generating these records and associated uncertainties are
discussed in the technical report:  Early_LaJolla_CO2_technical_report-1957-1962.pdf
The data file below contains 5 columns.  Column 1 is the sample date and column 2 is the
sample time. Column 3 is the decimal date of this sample date and time. Column 4 is the
interpolated index value. Column 5 is the interpolated CO2 concentration in micro-mol CO2
per mole (ppm) reported on the 2008A SIO manometric mole fraction scale.
Dates are local Pacific Standard time transcribed from datasheets
Date = day/month/year
Time = HH:MM where HH = hour and MM = minute
Decimal Date = fractional year of date and time
Index = index value, an initial data processing step created from raw voltages and
reference tank values
CO2 = ppm, calibrated on the '08A' X-scale as of Oct 1, 2013
